{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Authentication Flow","anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters: now, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"text":" value has been added to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"SessionConfiguration","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","isActive":true},{"text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"-related properties, named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","level":2,"anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned earlier, a new "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)":{"type":"topic","title":"init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/init(pdsurl:keychainprotocol:configuration:canresolve:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"Keychain","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"pdsURL","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"keychainProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Keychain